[thinking] 
[thinking] I need to consider that we shouldn't retest classes or logic flows already present. Perhaps the dynamic regex matcher is in the same class, but the "expected value regex" needs addressing. There’s also the idea of numeric comparison normalization, where JSONassert compares numbers like Integer/Long/Double as doubles, but that feature isn't fully covered yet. Additionally, unordered array comparison for simple value arrays with cardinality could be an uncovered feature. The existing lenient comparison doesn’t handle that aspect properly.
